## SCIENTIFIC MOTIVATION

### The Challenge

Roman's Galactic Bulge Survey will observe hundreds of millions of stars in crowded stellar environments.

These conditions create several challenges:

- Overlapping photometric signals
- Crowded-field contamination
- High false-positive risk
- Metadata provenance loss
- Limited interpretability of machine-learning outputs

Traditional pipelines frequently prioritize classification accuracy while providing limited visibility into intermediate reasoning steps.

